ndpointsDesired (GaugeVec), EndpointSliceSyncs (CounterVec)\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/metrics/metrics.go`: requestCounter (CounterVec), responseSizes (HistogramVec)\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/prometheus/workqueue/metrics.go`: depth, adds, unfinished metrics\n\n### Grafana/Grafana: Promauto Automatic Registration\n\nGrafana uses the `github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus/promauto` package for automatic metric registration, combined with per-component metrics constructors that accept a `prometheus.Registerer`.\n\n**Key Components:**\n- **Promauto Pattern**: `promauto.With(registerer).New<MetricType>()` for automatic registration with a specific registerer\n- **Alternative Global Pattern**: `promauto.New<MetricType>()` for metrics registered to the default registerer\n- **Metrics Structs**: Components define metrics in struct fields, initialized in constructor functions\n- **Metrics Constructor**: Functions like `NewSchedulerMetrics(r prometheus.Registerer)` return metrics structs\n- **Namespace/Subsystem**: Uses prometheus.CounterOpts, prometheus.HistogramOpts, prometheus.GaugeOpts with Name, Help, Namespace, Subsystem\n\n**Metric Registration Pattern**:\n1. Components define a metrics struct containing counter, gauge, histogram, and histogram fields\n2. Constructor function uses `promauto.With()` to wrap the registerer\n3. Metrics are created inline in the constructor using `promauto.With(r).NewCounterVec()` etc.\n4. Labels and options specified in prometheus.CounterOpts/HistogramOpts/GaugeOpts\n5. Automatic registration happens on creation (promauto behavior)\n\n**Example Files**:\n- `pkg/services/ngalert/metrics/scheduler.go`: NewSchedulerMetrics() with promauto.With(r).NewGauge(), NewCounterVec(), NewHistogramVec()\n- `pkg/infra/metrics/frontendmetrics.go`: registerFrontendHistogram() with manual registration via reg.MustRegister()\n- `pkg/infra/httpclient/httpclientprovider/prometheus_metrics_middleware.go`: NewPrometheusMetricsMiddleware() with manual register/MustRegister methods\n- `pkg/services/ngalert/metrics/api.go`: NewAPI() with promauto pattern for request duration histograms\n\n### Prometheus/Prometheus: Direct Registration with Registerer Interface\n\nPrometheus itself uses direct instantiation of metric collectors with explicit registration via the prometheus.Registerer interface. Metrics are organized into struct-based collectors that are instantiated with constructor functions.\n\n**Key Components:**\n- **Metric Structs**: Each component (notifier, tsdb, scrape, etc.) defines a struct holding its metrics\n- **Constructor Functions**: Functions like `newAlertMetrics()`, `newDBMetrics()` create and optionally register metrics\n- **Metric Creation**: Direct calls to `prometheus.NewCounter()`, `prometheus.NewHistogram()`, `prometheus.NewGaugeFunc()` etc.\n- **Registration Methods**: `registerer.MustRegister()` for component registrars, `prometheus.MustRegister()` for global registrations\n- **Gauge Functions**: Supports `prometheus.NewGaugeFunc()` for computed metrics that call a function on each scrape\n\n**Metric Registration Pattern**:\n1. Metrics structs defined in package (e.g., `alertMetrics`, `dbMetrics`, `queueManagerMetrics`)\n2. Constructor function creates all metric instances using `prometheus.New<Type>(prometheus.<Type>Opts{})`\n3. If registerer provided, metrics registered with `r.MustRegister(metric1, metric2, ...)`\n4. Metrics include namespace, subsystem, name, help, and sometimes custom labels or buckets\n5. GaugeFunc allows dynamic values computed at scrape time\n\n**Example Files**:\n- `notifier/metric.go`: newAlertMetrics() creates alertMetrics struct with SummaryVec, HistogramVec, CounterVec, GaugeVec, GaugeFunc\n- `tsdb/db.go`: newDBMetrics() creates dbMetrics with NewCounter(), NewGauge(), NewHistogram(), NewGaugeFunc()\n- `storage/remote/queue_manager.go`: queueManagerMetrics constructor with extensive gauges and counters\n- `cmd/prometheus/